TestAssertEqualsOmitsMessageWhenNotInStepText
/ Drift case 2 — the load-bearing reason this branch exists.
/
/ Step text `- assert %message% equals 'hello plang'` (Tests/Simple/Start.goal:6)
/ carries no custom error message. With os/system/modules/assert/module.notes.md
/ saying "omit Message from parameters and from formal unless the step text names
/ a custom error message; Expected is taken from the step text literal", the LLM
/ should emit:
/   parameters: { Expected: 'hello plang', Actual: %message% }   (no Message key)
/   formal contains Expected='hello plang' and no Message=...
/
/ Pre-fix shape this test forbids:
/   any Message key in parameters duplicating Expected            -- forbidden
/   Message='hello plang' in formal                               -- forbidden
/   formal='assert.equals(Expected=%!data%, ...)' (disagrees)     -- forbidden
/
/ Reads Tests/Simple/.build/start.pr and asserts. Architect's 3-fresh-cache rule
/ runs externally (see sibling drift case for the incantation).
- read file '/Tests/Simple/.build/start.pr', write to %pr%
- assert %pr% contains '"text": "assert %message% equals 'hello plang'"'
- assert %pr% does not contain '"name": "Message"'
- assert %pr% does not contain 'Expected=%!data%'
